Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on active, autonomous, and adaptive defense schemes to increase the attack cost and gather threat information. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses strategic learning schemes to estimate the unknown and reduce uncertainty in the defense strategies. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses reinforcement learning to converge to optimal defense policies in an autonomous and adaptive fashion. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses feedback-driven Moving Target Defense (MTD) as a defense scheme. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the design and implementation of defense schemes for cyber defense.
